      "message": "This is intended for drools as we have no consensus on using it globally.   In drools I need a concret domain model representation  to process policies in drl, etc ... I don't want to be parsing maps and list of strings for which I need to know its size and typecasting unvalidated objects and strings to something else.    \n\nThe difficulty that I find is that the comments are about an infrastructure that is not there yet, and even when built for drools I don't think will give me concrete domain object to operate with.",
